Bug 499228 - [Codegen Java] State-based incremental (Java Merger)

- Add JavaMerger that merges two java folders
- Code generator generates a tmp folder with new code, then merges with
existing folder before deleting tmp folder
- Comparison based on internal JDT implementation of JavaNode
- Supported java elements: package declaration, import container and
declaration, type, field, method
- If model has no method body, merge keeps the existing method body
- If model has no field initializer, merge keeps the existing field
initializer
- If created field has same name as existing field (but e.g. different
type), the existing field is deleted
- If model has no javadoc or its javadoc is contained in existing
javadoc, the existing javadoc is kept
- Enums are overwritten due to complexity of merging their constants,
fields, and operations
